02 Feb 2016 21:29






I sort of picture Dr Wondertainment as a little like the father/scientist from Cat's Cradle: Brilliant, but slightly senile and so wrapped up in his little mental world of rainbows and robot buddies and magic pets that he doesn't really think about the  or the consequences. He doesn't make anything out of malice or stupidity, just a dangerous mix of arcane knowledge, a sense of childlike wonder, and (at least partly willful) childlike naivete.

The Little Misters, though, I think of as a product of one of his lucid moments, where he knows that he's done harm and can see his daughter Isabel's growing corruption. These are his other children. Each embodies something that Dr Wondertainment wants to give the world- Laughter, Wonder, Whimsey, Curiosity, Creativity, Joy, Imagination, Adventure, Loveand yet each is flawed. Like it was tainted by something in Dr Wondertainment. Maybe by the part of him that created Mr. Redd. There's more to the story than whats been explored so far, and it needs to be told, I think.





